modules.description: Handles cookie-based session management and persistent storage for HTTP servers, using CoHTTP, Webmachine, Async, and Lwt. Operates on session identifiers, cookie headers, and backend storage structures like in-memory maps or file-based stores. Enables secure user authentication by tracking session state across requests, allowing restricted access until a user authenticates via a designated endpoint.

Provides functions to manage session data in a PostgreSQL database, including generating, retrieving, updating, and clearing sessions. Operates on strings for keys and values, with periods represented as 64-bit integers. Uses a dedicated table with a unique key and timestamp-based expiration for persistent session storage.
